    <note>Xie(1) Li [21483] When he was Nanxiong jun tuiguan, he traveled to Shaozhou and arranged the marriage between Tan(3) Shan [1587] and his daughter. His family was an hereditary classicist family and all the sons were taught classical scholarship (jingshu) and so were the daughters; all learned poetry (shi), documents (shu), ritual (li) and righteosness (yi) and no woman who became honored by a biography among the women of distinction (lienu) was not versed in antiquity. See Zheng Xia's funerary inscription for his daugher, wife of Tan(3) Shan [1587] (q.v.).</note>
